---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import HorizontalTimeline from "../../components/horizontal-timeline";
import { completedEvents } from "../../lib/events";
import { ArrowRight } from "lucide-react";
---

<Layout title="Commitments | North Star">

  <!-- Intro -->
  <header class="cm-intro">
    <h1 class="cm-intro-title">Imagine a future&hellip;</h1>
    <div class="cm-intro-prose">
      <p>AI and Robotics is moving faster than any institution can keep up with. Companies scramble to adapt and students graduate into a world their curriculum never prepared them for.</p>
      <p class="cm-intro-accent">The velocity gap widens every day.</p>
      <p>Knowledge is siloed, industries don&rsquo;t talk to each other and the people who should be building together have no way of connecting.</p>
      <p>North Star is an independent non-profit gathering and educating the generation that will inherit this world.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <nav class="cm-tabs" id="cm-tabs" aria-label="Commitments">
    <div class="cm-tabs-scroll">
      <a href="#events" class="cm-tab cm-tab-active" data-tab="events">Events</a>
      <a href="#education" class="cm-tab" data-tab="education">Education</a>
      <a href="#engineering" class="cm-tab" data-tab="engineering">Engineering</a>
      <a href="#ecosystem" class="cm-tab" data-tab="ecosystem">Ecosystem</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="cm-page">

    <!-- ═══ Events ═══ -->
    <section class="cm-section" id="events">
      <p class="cm-eyebrow">01 &middot; Events</p>
      <h2 class="cm-headline">Creating environments for sparks to ignite</h2>

      <div class="cm-prose">
        <p>An event is a dot. A community is a line. Dots don&rsquo;t compound. Lines do.</p>

        <p>The difference between a stalled ecosystem and a thriving one isn&rsquo;t talent or capital - it&rsquo;s whether the right people collide often enough for something to happen. When connection costs too much, lines never form. Belgium runs on dots. From time to time something happens, but if you&rsquo;re building in topics around AI or Robotics you might be out of luck for months.</p>

        <p>We host events because without them, the gap will keep widening. In our founding year we hosted 12 events, brought 800+ builders into the room, and over 20 hires were made through connections we created.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cm-timeline-wrap">
        <HorizontalTimeline client:load events={completedEvents} initialScrollTarget="end" compact />
      </div>

      <div class="cm-prose">
        <p>Read <a href="/blog/cost-of-connection" class="cm-link">Cost of Connection</a> - our argument for why creating rooms where technical people find each other is one of the highest-leverage interventions in an ecosystem.</p>
      </div>

    </section>

    <!-- ═══ Education ═══ -->
    <section class="cm-section" id="education">
      <p class="cm-eyebrow">02 &middot; Education</p>
      <h2 class="cm-headline">Do you remember the moment you knew what you wanted to do in life?</h2>

      <div class="cm-prose">
        <p>The velocity gap between how fast AI and Robotics moves and what people understand widens every day - it affects everyone.</p>

        <p>In 2025 we organized the Belgian chapter of the worldwide Kids AI Hackathon and it became the biggest edition on the planet - 8 venues across 6 cities, 80 volunteers and 100 kids building with AI for the first time. These kids are growing up in an AI-native world and our job is to make sure they don&rsquo;t just consume it but learn to build with it. In 20 years, they will be the ones writing this website.</p>

        <p>For students, the fear of AI is pushing people away from STEM at the exact moment the world needs more of them. Enrollment is dropping while demand for AI and Robotics talent accelerates. Robotics can be the bridge - it gives code a physical form, and in the coming years it will be the catalyst that puts the Benelux on the map. Through workshops, hackathons and direct access to practitioners, we give students a practical on-ramp alongside their education.</p>

        <p>For professionals, Belgium runs on SMEs, automation is their biggest AI opportunity but the gap between knowing that and knowing what to do about it is where most companies stall. We give teams the understanding to either define what they need or build it themselves.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cm-gallery">
        <a href="/events/kids-ai-vibecoding-hackathon" class="cm-fig"><img src="/kids-hackathon/Multi-design Misc (1).png" alt="Kids AI Hackathon" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Kids AI Hackathon</figcaption></a>
        <a href="/work-with-us#contact" class="cm-fig"><img src="/misc/future-is-you.png" alt="The Future Is You" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>The Future Is You</figcaption></a>
        <a href="/events/openclaw-deep-dive" class="cm-fig"><img src="/openclaw-meetup/photo_2026-03-08 19.28.34.jpeg" alt="OpenClaw Deep Dive" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>OpenClaw Deep Dive</figcaption></a>
      </div>

    </section>

    <!-- ═══ Engineering ═══ -->
    <section class="cm-section" id="engineering">
      <p class="cm-eyebrow">03 &middot; Engineering</p>
      <h2 class="cm-headline">Heart of a Builder</h2>

      <div class="cm-prose">
        <p>Every member of our core team builds. We have a bias towards action and an engineering mindset that strips every problem down to its simplest form before solving it. Without building, the rest is just conversation.</p>

        <p>Every product we&rsquo;ve made started as a problem we hit ourselves (<a href="https://etoile.tech" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cm-etoile-link"><img src="/etoile-logo.png" alt="Etoile" class="cm-etoile-logo" /></a>, <a href="https://discord.gg/m5Hknymurb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cm-etoile-link"><img src="/team/polaris.png" alt="Polaris" class="cm-polaris-logo" /></a>). That same drive extends to companies - through R&amp;D residencies we explore and prototype solutions fast, either by embedding with a team or by running a hackathon around their problem.</p>

        <p>Our robotics team is our pride and joy. We&rsquo;ve worked on humanoids, industrial arms, robot dogs and SO-101 LeRobot arms. In 10 years these machines will become more and more a part of our daily lives, and by having access to them we have a duty to show people what&rsquo;s coming - to give a glimpse into a future that&rsquo;s closer than we think.</p>

      </div>

      <div class="cm-gallery">
        <a href="/events/future-in-bloom-pt1" class="cm-fig"><img src="/future-in-bloom/1.jpg" alt="Future in Bloom" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Future in Bloom</figcaption></a>
        <a href="https://thevessel.be" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cm-fig"><img src="/misc/photo_2026-03-08 21.51.25.jpeg" alt="Aegis" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Project Aegis</figcaption></a>
        <a href="https://thevessel.be" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cm-fig"><img src="/misc/photo_2026-03-08 21.53.26.jpeg" alt="Brainstorm" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Brainstorm</figcaption></a>
      </div>

    </section>

    <!-- ═══ Ecosystem ═══ -->
    <section class="cm-section" id="ecosystem">
      <p class="cm-eyebrow">04 &middot; Ecosystem</p>
      <h2 class="cm-headline">We&rsquo;re in this together</h2>

      <div class="cm-prose">
        <p>Some of the strongest builder ecosystems in Europe are a train ride away - London, Paris, Amsterdam. The potential of connecting them is enormous and largely untapped.</p>

        <p>This isn&rsquo;t something one non-profit can solve alone. North Star is an independent non-profit - we&rsquo;re not tied to anything or anyone. We partner with builder communities across Europe because different ecosystems have different strengths, and connecting them makes everyone stronger.</p>

        <p>Sponsorships are one of the ways we fund these operations, and every partner who backs us is investing in the infrastructure that connects builders across Belgium and Europe.</p>

        <p>Belgium has a very important role to play in the coming years. As a bridge between ecosystems, as the heart of the European Union where a strong builder community has direct proximity to the policymakers shaping AI and Robotics regulation, and as a testbed for the next chapter of robotics - with a university density, port infrastructure and logistics network that no other region in Europe combines in such a small area.</p>

        <p>We&rsquo;re here as a grassroots catalyst to make it happen.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cm-gallery">
        <a href="/events/robotics-hackathon-i" class="cm-fig"><img src="/misc/SCR-20260308-stfw.jpeg" alt="HuggingFace Paris" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>HuggingFace, Paris</figcaption></a>
        <a href="/events/tectonic" class="cm-fig"><img src="/tectonic/SCR-20260308-stdv.jpeg" alt="Tectonic Conference" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Tectonic</figcaption></a>
        <a href="/events/elevenlabs-hackathon-ghent" class="cm-fig"><img src="/elevenlabs/1.jpg" alt="ElevenLabs Ghent" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>ElevenLabs Ghent</figcaption></a>
      </div>

      <div class="cm-form-wrap">
        <h3 class="cm-form-title">Get involved</h3>
        <iframe
          data-tally-src="https://tally.so/embed/0QMBQ6?alignLeft=1&hideTitle=1&transparentBackground=1&dynamicHeight=1"
          loading="lazy"
          width="100%"
          height="877"
          frameborder="0"
          marginheight="0"
          marginwidth="0"
          title="Partner with North Star"
        ></iframe>
      </div>

      <script is:inline>
        var d=document,w="https://tally.so/widgets/embed.js",v=function(){"undefined"!=typeof Tally?Tally.loadEmbeds():d.querySelectorAll("iframe[data-tally-src]:not([src])").forEach(function(e){e.src=e.dataset.tallySrc})};if("undefined"!=typeof Tally)v();else if(d.querySelector('script[src="'+w+'"]')==null){var s=d.createElement("script");s.src=w,s.onload=v,s.onerror=v,d.body.appendChild(s);}
      </script>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  /* ── Intro ── */
  .cm-intro {
    max-width: 660px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(8rem, 18vh, 14rem) 1.5rem clamp(3rem, 6vh, 5rem);
  }

  .cm-intro-title {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1.5rem, 3vh, 2.5rem);
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .cm-intro-prose p {
    font-family: "Geist", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(0.94rem, 1.2vw, 1.08rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.48);
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .cm-intro-prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cm-intro-accent {
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif !important;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.5rem) !important;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82) !important;
    line-height: 1.3 !important;
    margin-top: 1.6rem !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.6rem !important;
  }

  /* ── Events timeline ── */
  .cm-timeline-wrap {
    margin: 2rem -1.5rem 2.5rem;
  }

  /* ── Sticky tab bar ── */
  .cm-tabs {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 40;
    background: rgba(15, 14, 12, 0.96);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(140%);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(140%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    padding-top: calc(env(safe-area-inset-top) + 3.2rem);
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .cm-tabs { padding-top: 4.5rem; }
  }

  .cm-tabs-scroll {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    gap: 0.15rem;
  }

  .cm-tab {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding: 0.42rem 0.9rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 180ms ease, background 180ms ease;
  }
  .cm-tab:hover { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6); }
  .cm-tab-active {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
  }

  /* ── Page container ── */
  .cm-page {
    max-width: 660px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 0;
  }

  /* ── Sections ── */
  .cm-section {
    padding: clamp(4rem, 8vh, 6rem) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    scroll-margin-top: calc(env(safe-area-inset-top) + 6.5rem);
  }
  .cm-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: clamp(5rem, 10vh, 8rem);
  }
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .cm-section { scroll-margin-top: 7rem; }
  }

  /* ── Typography ── */
  .cm-eyebrow {
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.58);
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
  }

  .cm-headline {
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.2vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  /* ── Prose blocks ── */
  .cm-prose {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .cm-prose p {
    font-family: "Geist", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(0.94rem, 1.1vw, 1.04rem);
    line-height: 1.78;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .cm-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .cm-prose strong {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cm-link {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.68);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18);
    transition: color 180ms ease, border-color 180ms ease;
  }
  .cm-link:hover {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
  }

  .cm-etoile-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    vertical-align: middle;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: none;
    transition: opacity 200ms ease, transform 200ms ease;
  }
  .cm-etoile-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .cm-etoile-logo {
    height: 1.1em;
    width: auto;
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
    position: relative;
    top: -0.05em;
    filter: brightness(1.1);
  }
  .cm-polaris-logo {
    height: 1.4em;
    width: 1.4em;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
    position: relative;
    top: -0.05em;
  }

  /* ── Gallery — 3-image layout with captions ── */
  .cm-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3fr 2fr;
    grid-template-rows: 160px 160px;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .cm-fig {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
  }
  .cm-fig img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    filter: brightness(0.75) saturate(0.65);
    transition: filter 500ms ease;
  }
  .cm-fig:hover img { filter: brightness(0.95) saturate(1); }

  .cm-fig figcaption {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    padding: 1.2rem 0.55rem 0.4rem;
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7) 0%, transparent 100%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* 1st image: tall left column spanning both rows */
  .cm-fig:nth-child(1) { grid-column: 1; grid-row: 1 / 3; }
  /* 2nd image: top right */
  .cm-fig:nth-child(2) { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1; }
  /* 3rd image: bottom right */
  .cm-fig:nth-child(3) { grid-column: 2; grid-row: 2; }

  /* ── CTA row ── */
  .cm-form-wrap {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    max-width: 600px;
  }
  .cm-form-title {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-family: "Instrument Serif", serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82);
  }
  .cm-form-wrap iframe {
    border: none;
    width: 100%;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .cm-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: 160px 120px 120px;
    }
    .cm-fig:nth-child(1) { grid-column: 1; grid-row: 1; }
    .cm-fig:nth-child(2) { grid-column: 1; grid-row: 2; }
    .cm-fig:nth-child(3) { grid-column: 1; grid-row: 3; }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  (function () {
    var tabs = document.querySelectorAll(".cm-tab");
    var sections = document.querySelectorAll(".cm-section");
    if (!tabs.length || !sections.length) return;

    var io = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
      entries.forEach(function (entry) {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          var id = entry.target.id;
          tabs.forEach(function (tab) {
            if (tab.getAttribute("data-tab") === id) {
              tab.classList.add("cm-tab-active");
            } else {
              tab.classList.remove("cm-tab-active");
            }
          });
        }
      });
    }, { rootMargin: "-40% 0px -55% 0px" });

    sections.forEach(function (s) { io.observe(s); });
  })();
</script>
